<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id0e673937-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s9580"><num value="9580">§ 9580.</num><heading> Voluntary service</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Director may accept voluntary and uncompensated services to carry out and support activities that are consistent with the priorities and mission of the Institute.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id0e673938-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795">(<ref href="/us/pl/107/279/tI/s190">Pub. L. 107–279, title I, § 190</ref>, <date date="2002-11-05">Nov. 5, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/1974">116 Stat. 1974</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
